A vintage-style illustration of an industrial bakery assembly line viewed from above, showing a single cheesecake moving along a weathered conveyor belt through distinct processing stations. At each station, aged paper documents with stamps and handwritten notes accumulate and stack beneath the cake like layers of history. The color palette features warm sepia tones, faded creams, and dusty rose pinks. Brass gears and mechanical pulleys connect the stations, with wisps of flour dust catching golden afternoon light streaming through tall factory windows. The papers beneath the cheesecake grow progressively thicker and more layered as it travels forward, creating a visual metaphor of accumulated knowledge and provenance following the product through its journey.
